  <histories>
	<history>
	  <header>Origin Story</header>
	  <text>
		Pile Up began as a student project and the team formed deep bonds during development. We discovered a shared need for cooperation adventures and feel-good experiences. Pile Up became the center of all our lives for the 6 months we spent working on it. We established a common vision which we are all excited and motivated to complete. And since October 2019, we are working hard to give life to Pile Up through our studio, Seed by Seed!
		All of us are juniors with some experience in the industry and many personal projects under our belt. We all have different skills which complement each other! Oh! And we are French by the way! We are settled in the city of Angoulême.
	  </text>
	</history>
	<history>
	  <header>Design Philosophy</header>
      <text>
        At Seed By Seed, we believe that games are a good way to create bounds between people. When we created this project, we thought there is a need in the industry for more cooperative games. Especially for casual games and children-oriented games. This was our core intention:  the promise of an adventure that you could share with up to four people, a casual game that could gather the whole family, children and parents alike, in a funny, playful and non-violent space.
      </text>
	</history>
  </histories>
  

